title: Allison Kneisel
text:
Welcome!
I study aquatic systems to:

1) Understand how the watershed context of lakes, ponds, and wetlands influence their structure, function, and ecosystem service supply.

2) Explore how these systems are changing through time in response to changing land use, climate, and other drivers.
I am currently a PhD Candidate at the University of Wisconsin – Madison in the Ecosystem and Landscape Ecology Lab where I am studying carbon in urban ponds, wetland ecosystem services, and lake temporal dynamics in the Upper Midwest of the US with Dr. Monica Turner.
